  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In some models, there is a button on the glasses or very simple controls to select options and for limited movement through the virtual environment.",
    "Depending on the Degrees Of Freedom (DOF), (i.e., possible movements within the virtual space) applications can be 3DOF or 6DOF (Rossi et al. 2021):",
    "• 3DOF: these degrees of freedom correspond to the rotation of the head in its different axes (x, y, and z).",
    "The interaction with the environment is only possible by changing the viewing direction, i.e., looking up, down, sideways, and tilting the head from side to side.",
    "• 6DOF: compared to 3DOF, they add movement in all three axes (x, y, and z) to the 3DOF previously explained."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Depending on the Degrees Of Freedom (DOF), (i.e., possible movements within the virtual space) applications can be 3DOF or 6DOF (Rossi et al. 2021):"
  ]
